  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The behavior of copydb ( or fast sync) is to sync state tree in the block of `current height - 64`, but it seems geth don't persist state tree in the block of `current height - 64` before exist (it only persist `current height`, `current height - 1`, `current height - 127`) . So copydb will panic.\r\n\r\nIf I panic in copydb, I have to start geth and wait it syncing another 64 blocks and exist. Then invoke copydb again, it will work normally.",
